Ranger Help for: wilderness
============================

SUMMARY:
The Wilderness branch covers the Ranger's survival and crafting skills.
These abilities allow a Ranger to live off the land, create tools and
weapons from natural materials, and navigate the wilds with ease.

Key wilderness skills include:

  Forage          - Search for edible plants and herbs
  Harvest Wood    - Gather wood from trees for crafting
  Skin Animal     - Skin a corpse for meat and hide
  Carve Bow       - Craft a bow from wood and rope
  Carve Arrow     - Carve arrows from harvested wood
  Make Torch      - Create a torch for light
  Make Rope       - Craft rope from natural materials
  Make Fish Trap   - Weave a trap for catching camp fish
  Build Shelter   - Construct a camp shelter for resting
  Use Herbs       - Apply gathered herbs to heal or cure
  Calm Animal     - Soothe an aggressive animal
  Call Follower   - Summon your bonded animal companion
  Train Animal    - Teach your follower new tricks
  Adapt           - Adapt your body to extreme climates

A Ranger who masters wilderness skills can survive indefinitely in
even the harshest environments without depending on civilization.

